Mobile application for users on the move. Provides acute measurements/alerts by monitoring vital signs (heart rate, posture and activity). By taking into account the user profile, the application informs the user for any potential health problems and sends a notification alert (e.g. SMS) with the GPS location to the formal/informal caregiver.

Several studies have reported mild cognitive impairment differences in language tests yet few studies have characterized or compare these subtypes in more detailed linguistic features beyond the traditional language–speech and semantic impairment such as sentence production, case markers processing and verbs. This groups of tools (can be seen as one tool with multiple levels) investigates the relationship between cognitive decline (multi-domain MCI and single MCI) and sentence production/narrative comprehension with contextual information. Results can provide useful information regarding which individuals are at greatest risk for further cognitive decline, or if they need to attend clinical intervention

MLS Multimedia SA (MLS) was established in Thessaloniki, Greece in 1995 
    aiming at the development of web technologies, telematics applications, 
    multimedia software and software protection. MLS is the inventor of the 
    MLS Laserlock software protection system and has been
awarded the 1998 European Information Technology Grand Prize Winner. MLS has 
    developed “MLS Destinator Talk&Drive” that is the leading Navigation 
    product in the Greek Market (60% market share). MLS Talk&Drive utilizes 
    speech recognition & synthesis as a primary interface for the user. 
    It’s integrated into a number of different devices, such as PDAs, smartphones 
    and tablets. MLS is also the largest company in development, publishing 
    and distributing of Greek Multimedia titles in Greece. In July 2012, MLS 
    released in the Greek market the first Greek
Android Smartphone and Tablet with Artificial Intelligence & Voice 
    Recognition. MLS has developed and acquired over the years significant 
    expertise on Intelligent and Audiovisual
Navigation Systems through competitive research activity with international 
    partners supported by
both European and national funding.
